cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and their ability to learn human-like word order preferences. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of RNNs for language modeling. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are possible sub-categories as they both deal with the development and use of neural networks. Finally, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely sub-category as it is not directly related to the topic of the paper.
